the press, but soon realizes that his reputation&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:30.000
could be plagued by the others who were around&nbsp;
him. At Katerina's funeral, he meets Margaret,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:34.240
who claims she could tell that Whip was drunk&nbsp;
when she encountered him that morning. Whip&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:34.240 --> 00:07:39.120
then starts to get personal, claiming that if not&nbsp;
for him, she could have ended up dead as well.
&nbsp;

00:07:39.120 --> 00:07:43.600
Whip then visits Ken at the hospital.&nbsp;
Ken explains he hasn't told the NTSB,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:43.600 --> 00:07:48.320
who have been investigating the crash, about&nbsp;
his suspicions on Whip's condition at the time.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:51.680
Ken knows what Margaret does, Whip was hung over&nbsp;
in the cockpit and that he may have been drunk&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:51.680 --> 00:07:56.400
when the accident occurred. Even though he may&nbsp;
